body:
### Motivation

Fix: #10021 #11197

Websocket service should provide the encryption context to its consumers, so that they can perform manual decryption of the message payloads.

An example of encryption context:

```json
{
  "messageId": "CAMQADAA",
  "payload": "hvXcJvHW7kOSrUn17P2q71RA5SdiXwZBqw==",
  "properties": {},
  "publishTime": "2021-10-29T16:01:38.967-07:00",
  "redeliveryCount": 0,
  "encryptionContext": {
    "keys": {
      "client-rsa.pem": {
        "keyValue": "",
        "metadata": {}
      }
    },
    "param": "Tfu1PxVm6S9D3+Hk",
    "compressionType": "NONE",
    "uncompressedMessageSize": 0,
    "batchSize": {
      "empty": false,
      "present": true
    }
  }
}
```
